title: Add support for Ollama, Palm, Claude-2, Cohere, Replicate Llama2 CodeLlama (100+LLMs) - using LiteLLM
body:
This PR adds support for the above mentioned LLMs using LiteLLM https://github.com/BerriAI/litellm/ 
LiteLLM is a lightweight package to simplify LLM API calls - use any llm as a drop in replacement for gpt-3.5-turbo. 


Example
```python
from litellm import completion

## set ENV variables
os.environ["OPENAI_API_KEY"] = "openai key"
os.environ["COHERE_API_KEY"] = "cohere key"

messages = [{ "content": "Hello, how are you?","role": "user"}]

# openai call
response = completion(model="gpt-3.5-turbo", messages=messages)

# cohere call
response = completion(model="command-nightly", messages)

# anthropic call
response = completion(model="claude-instant-1", messages=messages)
```

title: vllm support
body:
Enables support for vLLM. To use, you must specify the `model` field in the `task` parameter of the `pgml.transform` function **and** you must add `"backend": "vllm"` in the `task` parameters. For example,

```sql
SELECT * FROM pgml.transform(
    task => '{"model":"tiiuae/falcon-7b","backend":"vllm"}'::JSONB,
    inputs => Array['hello']
);
```

A list of supported models for vLLM can be found [here](https://vllm.readthedocs.io/en/latest/models/supported_models.html).

Only one vLLM model can be loaded per client connection process due to a [limitation in vLLM](https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/issues/565). The first call to `pgml.transform` with a given model will load the model ("cold start"), but subsequent calls will use the cached model. If you change the specified model in the same client connection, the cached model will be replaced with the new one.
